song_name: Fooling Yourself The Angry Young Man

version_description: Https://youtu.be/0RZNBEfXVkI The intro is no chords, drums only. The walkdown signature riff is the D is played on the 14th fret, the A on the 9th fret (D shape), and the G on the 7th fret (D shape) to sound like the album. However, for acoustic covers it sounds fine to play all the chords regular. If you have two guitarists one can play the iconic walkdown, and another can just play regular D, A, G chords behind.
Detailed Instrumentals - 12 beats in intro instrumental lead on C. Second instrumental is eight beats. Fm end of measure is a drum run. Bridge is clear chunk guitar solo. Instrumental 3 is 16 beat.
